<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-42DCAC25-3621-40AE-B100-32861107EDF7" version="1" lang="en-US"?><concept xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-42DCAC25-3621-40AE-B100-32861107EDF7" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic concept)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c concept oceConcept-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic concept/concept "><title class="- topic/title ">12 The function of the media loading drawer</title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="GUID-34C6A3E5-E809-4139-80CC-275A8CCF9EDC"><p class="- topic/p ">The media loading drawer holds the rolls of media and feeds the media into the input unit. 
</p><fig class="- topic/fig " id="GUID-E8E6B03A-14B8-4CFE-9E12-601DAFFE494A"><image class="- topic/image " href="GUID-D8B67152-00EB-44C9-BCA3-5CFA3F417974-low.png" id="IMAGE_0E055DC80ADB43AE995D880491942C2B" placement="inline" otherprops="GUID-D8B67152-00EB-44C9-BCA3-5CFA3F417974-low.png"/></fig></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Functional description</category></metadata></prolog><conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody "><section id="GUID-F5034822-753A-4C8B-A7CD-E44CE7EBD702" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Media rolls</title><p class="- topic/p ">The media loading drawer can hold two media rolls. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The media rolls can be 64 inch wide, and can have a diameter of up to 220 mm. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Media rolls can weigh up to 50 kg and it takes 2 people to load a media roll. You can also use an external lifting tool. 
</p><fig id="GUID-CF83F173-0160-4751-B0D8-B1CB000E57A7" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-9CC90B3E-B72A-4492-8BC6-6E1256FB57C4-low.png" id="IMAGE_5D4FC55AAED443D6BA547529870C2246" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-9CC90B3E-B72A-4492-8BC6-6E1256FB57C4-low.png"/></fig></section><section id="GUID-8EEF2870-A5FF-4754-9E6E-02D0B8F2C412" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Inserting the media in the media loading drawer</title><fig id="GUID-27A9AA17-C593-4F13-B86D-C0362E9A3158" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-FAFF5410-176C-49DB-A5CC-3CA16326E056-low.png" id="IMAGE_6C35650D9C3541929A5B43A61AA2B607" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-FAFF5410-176C-49DB-A5CC-3CA16326E056-low.png"/></fig><ol id="OL_5A1178085EFC454EBA0AD33B6FAE4BBA" class="- topic/ol "><li id="LI_002180EA3812413EAB1E37CA81DAF287" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Load the media roll. 
</p></li><li id="LI_2907E4F3970D4317A9DA08509B4E8FE9" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Feed the media into the media path manually. 
</p></li><li id="LI_EA5A1294489546ABAB38F22DD9BFB8F9" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> When the media reaches sensor 1 the media loading pinch (MLO) starts to run. 
</p></li><li id="LI_DAF499E08D1241B3AA346A1FE18626FC" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">The media is now fed by the media loading pinch until the media reaches sensor 2. 
</p></li><li id="LI_CFF897B3700C466FBAB9C858D442A01D" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">A beep signal is made and the media loading pinch now reverses direction until sensor 2 is free again. 
</p></li><li id="LI_71B96C73B3F3458D8E45F4420AFC15EC" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> This is the normal start position for media in the media loading drawer. 
</p></li></ol><table id="GUID-7D022BB4-8DF2-4FF2-9A93-3212D9E8DC59" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Roll 1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Roll 2 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Sensor 1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Media loading drawer 1 roll 1 sensor 1</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 12B1 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">MLO_DRA1_ROL1_SE1</compsignal></comp> 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Media loading drawer 1 roll 2 sensor 1</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 12B6 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">MLO_DRA1_ROL2_SE1</compsignal></comp> 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Sensor 2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Media loading drawer 1 roll 1 sensor 2</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 12B2 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">MLO_DRA1_ROL1_SE2</compsignal></comp> 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Media loading drawer 1 roll 2 sensor 2</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 12B7 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">MLO_DRA1_ROL2_SE2</compsignal></comp> 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">MLO 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Media loading drawer 1 pinch 1 motor</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 12M2 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">MLO_DRA1_PINCH1_MO</compsignal></comp> 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Media loading drawer 1 pinch 2 motor</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 12M4 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">MLO_DRA1_PINCH2_MO</compsignal></comp> 
</p></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-74CC6153-F805-47F6-82E0-DEC50C13C327" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "> First media use after insertion </title><p class="- topic/p "> First media use after insertion( media roll initialization). On the first use after a media is inserted, the leading edge of the media is fed and retracted 3 times before feeding it to print surface. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">These 3 media movements are done to determine the motor control parameters and the outer radius of the inserted roll. This is used to determine the feed speed of the roll motor during printing and as input for the remaining media length calculation. 
</p></section><section id="GUID-137EB685-5D9C-46A5-B43E-AEAB9BA4D284" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Feeding of the media during printing</title><p class="- topic/p ">Each media roll has its own drive motor. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">During printing these drive motors are running at the same speed as <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">X motion system drive motor</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 15M1 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">XMS_DRV_MO</compsignal></comp>. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Eventual speed differences are compensated by the buffer unit. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The speed of the roll motor is detected by the motor encoder. 
</p><table id="GUID-9BBF58B8-D0F0-4072-B362-C01C59CE2F1F" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Roll 1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Roll 2 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Drive motor 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Media loading drawer 1 roll 1 motor</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 12M1 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">MLO_DRA1_ROL1_MO</compsignal></comp> 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Media loading drawer 1 roll 2 motor</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 12M3 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">MLO_DRA1_ROL2_MO</compsignal></comp> 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Motor encoder 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Media loading drawer 1 roll 1 motor encoder</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 12B3 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">MLO_DRA1_ROL1_MO_ENC</compsignal></comp> 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Media loading drawer 1 roll 2 motor encoder</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 12B8 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">MLO_DRA1_ROL2_MO_ENC</compsignal></comp> 
</p></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="SECTION_415AD112623C4BE2B7A360D7B3113C92" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Detection of the amount of media left on the rolls</title><p class="- topic/p "> To determine the amount of media that is on the roll the outer media diameter, the outer roll core diameter and the media thickness must be known. Also known as remaining media length. The engine uses initially the values that are inserted by the customer. While using the media the engine determines those values more precise and will use only its internally determined values. For media (per width and type) initially confidence on the measurements has to be built up. Until that time unknown is shown on the user interface. When confidence is built up, it will take max 3 roll revolutions on a roll insert of same media type and width. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> The outer roll core diameter is determined by a roll empty, the value is used until the next roll empty is detected. In case of an unexpected roll empty this value might be wrong resulting in an unexpected value. This will resolve itself by the next roll empty. The MLO pinch encoder and the roll motor are used to determine the outer roll diameter and the media thickness. The media thickness is only updated when a roll is retracted. 
</p><table id="GUID-DDEC45B4-AA2B-40BF-8986-90A2240F11FB" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Roll 1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Roll 2 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">MLO pinch encoder 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Media loading drawer 1 pinch 1 encoder</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 12B5 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">MLO_DRA1_PINCH1_ENC</compsignal></comp> 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Media loading drawer 1 pinch 2 encoder</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 12B10 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">MLO_DRA1_PINCH2_ENC</compsignal></comp> 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Motor encoder 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Media loading drawer 1 roll 1 motor encoder</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 12B3 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">MLO_DRA1_ROL1_MO_ENC</compsignal></comp> 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Media loading drawer 1 roll 2 motor encoder</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 12B8 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">MLO_DRA1_ROL2_MO_ENC</compsignal></comp> 
</p></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="SECTION_91A973B6EC36483E90A4386501006546" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">End of roll handling</title><p class="- topic/p ">There are 2 different types of End of roll that can happen : 
</p><ol id="OL_6B65B27A110B4B1C84216913BF67E16F" class="- topic/ol "><li id="LI_8A26BB68F19445B7B825C5E2FD2C22E7" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">End of roll when the media is fixed to the core. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">When end of roll happens the feed of media from the roll drawers stops abruptly. The buffer will move inward very quickly and printing stops immediately. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> The X motion system buffer left encoder and the X motion system buffer right encoder will be triggered. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> The operator must cut the media at the buffer plate and remove the media with uncured ink as chemical waste! 
</p></li><li id="LI_82C06750A6384E03A9928C803A7AFB8A" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">End of roll where the media is loose on the core. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> When the end of roll is near the media usually starts to slip on the core. The buffer plate will move outwards very quickly. This is detected by the right and left buffer encoder. The printer will stop printing and feed the media through to finish curing. 
</p></li></ol><table id="GUID-1D5DB5FD-FB97-484B-9E5A-529C5F21EDDC" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="2" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Short name 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Component name 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Left buffer encoder 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">X motion system buffer left encoder</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 15B9 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">XMS_BUF_LEFT_ENC</compsignal></comp> 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Right buffer encoder 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">X motion system buffer right encoder</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 15B10 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">XMS_BUF_RIGHT_ENC</compsignal></comp> 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Sensor in roll 1 to determine roll empty 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Media loading drawer 1 roll 1 sensor 1</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 12B1 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">MLO_DRA1_ROL1_SE1</compsignal></comp> 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Sensor in roll 2 to determine roll empty 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Media loading drawer 1 roll 2 sensor 1</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 12B6 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">MLO_DRA1_ROL2_SE1</compsignal></comp> 
</p></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-5F4CB8EC-CF92-4289-A0E3-7368F81D5FBB" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Inside and outside printing</title><p class="- topic/p ">There are two print sides supported: 
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Print side out (standard) 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Print side in 
</p></li></ul><p class="- topic/p ">Media transport in the media drawer 
</p><table id="GUID-E207732C-CBF8-460C-A73E-99FC14667113" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="2" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Description 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">View 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Print side out printing</b> 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> The standard way is to use "Print side out". 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> This is supported by both roll positions: roll 1 and roll2. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">In this mode, two rolls can be loaded in parallel. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-E0EB2F91-BEAD-4633-AA2B-6F93CBA3CF19" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-CA33CDD7-2640-448D-86EF-A874980C792E-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-CA33CDD7-2640-448D-86EF-A874980C792E-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> "Print side in" makes use the sensors and pinch motor of roll position 1 and the drive of roll position 2. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> This option needs both roll positions for 1 media roll. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-D60D58D1-3829-479B-BC0A-F8FA9482BD36" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-BF5B5C02-6938-4456-A2FC-DB1A6587DFAB-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-BF5B5C02-6938-4456-A2FC-DB1A6587DFAB-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> The printer detects the print side of the media automatically during loading. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Media is loaded into roll position 2 'reverse winding'. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Media is inserted into the media path of roll position1. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> The media is seen by SE1, the pinch motor transports it to SE2 and a beep is produced. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> When the drawer is closed, the drive motor of roll position 1 is trying to retract the media. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> If SE2 becomes inactive, the printer knows the media is loaded "print side out". 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> If SE2 doesn't become inactive, the drive motor of roll position 2 is trying to retract media. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> If SE2 becomes inactive, the printer knows the media is loaded "print side in". 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> This is reflected by a different icon on the operator media screen. 
